  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">The Weymouth Female Anti-Slavery Society wants the use of the Orthodox Meeting House &quot;for the purpose of hearing an Anti-Slavery lecture from Mr. Garrison.&quot; Anne W. Weston explains why the request is made every year even though is is always refused. The Universalist Meeting House is available, but the orthodox parishioners won&apos;t go there. The pro-slavery orthodox churches protect their followers from anti-slavery doctrine. &quot;Could the infamous war with Mexico continue another month were all the churches of the Free states thrown freely open to the Anti-Slavery lectures?&quot; She gives general arguments in favor of allowing the abolitionists to use the church.</subfield>
